<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="conservation status">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Conservation status in Cameroon.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. Cusset, Adansonia ser 2, 14 (2): 275" authorityYear="1974" baseAuthorityName="G. Taylor" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Podostemaceae" genus="Ledermanniella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ledermanniella variabilis" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="variabilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Ledermanniella variabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is listed on http://www.iucnredlist.org as Endangered (
<bibRefCitation author="Ghogue, J-P" journalOrPublisher="Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" refId="B40" refString="Ghogue, J-P, 2010l. Ledermanniellavariabilis. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2010: e.T185224A8370407. [Downloaded on 20 August 2018]" title="Ledermanniellavariabilis. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2010: e. T 185224 A 8370407. [Downloaded on 20 August 2018]" year="2010 l">Ghogue 2010l</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Onana, JM" journalOrPublisher="Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" refId="B66" refString="Onana, JM, Cheek, M, 2011. Red data list of the flowering plants of Cameroon: IUCN Global Assessments. Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew" title="Red data list of the flowering plants of Cameroon: IUCN Global Assessments." year="2011">Onana and Cheek (2011)</bibRefCitation>
reassessed this species as Endangered. The species is known from two localities and the area of occupancy and extent of occurrence are estimated to be less than 10 km2 each. The Lobe waterfall locality is a famous tourist attraction so there is a continuous decline in the quality of the habitat at this site. The species is here reassessed as Critically Endangered. IUCN Red List Category: 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Critically Endangered CRB1+2ab (ii, iii).</emphasis>
</paragraph>
